<link href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css" id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark"/>
</head>
<body>
<button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
<div class="osce-protocol">
<details>
<summary class="h3">EXPAND: DNACPR DISCUSSION - OSCE PROTOCOL (SPIKES FRAMEWORK)</summary>
<div class="video-container">
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KowT-7aEoZA" title="DNACPR Discussion - OSCE Guide"></iframe>
</div>
<p><em>(<b>Scenario:</b> A junior doctor discusses future care planning, specifically a DNACPR order, with the daughter of an elderly patient with multiple comorbidities.)</em></p>
<h4>S: Setting up the Interview</h4>
<ul>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Introduce yourself &amp; your role</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Hi there, my name's Leah, I'm one of the junior doctors working on Ward 36." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=10s">0:10</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Confirm relative's identity &amp; relationship</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Could I just check your name and ask how you're related to Mrs. Brown, please?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=14s">0:14</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Confirm patient's details (Safety Check)</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Could I just double-check, do you know Mrs. Brown's date of birth for me?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=23s">0:23</a>)</span></div>
</ul>
<h4>P: Assessing Perception</h4>
<ul>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Explore their understanding of the patient's current situation (ICE)</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Can I just check what you understand about your mum's condition so far?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=42s">0:42</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Summarise their understanding to establish a shared baseline</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"So as you said, your mum's come into hospital with a chest infection this time... it seems like she is getting better..." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=116s">1:56</a>)</span></div>
</ul>
<h4>I: Obtaining an Invitation</h4>
<ul>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Explore their expectation for the meeting</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Were you aware about what we were going to be talking about today?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=101s">1:41</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Signpost the difficult nature of the conversation</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Sometimes when we're talking about planning for the future... we also think about what might happen if your mum was to come back into hospital... if she was much more unwell..." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=133s">2:13</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Seek permission to proceed with the discussion</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Are you happy if we talk a bit more about that now?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=177s">2:57</a>)</span></div>
</ul>
<h4>K: Giving Knowledge &amp; Information</h4>
<ul>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Introduce the specific term "DNACPR"</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Sometimes in the context of that planning, we think about something called a DNACPR. Have you ever heard of that before?" (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=160s">2:40</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Explain the reality and low success rate of CPR in this specific patient context</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"Sometimes CPR is not successful, as it often is shown on the television... often it's not successful in people who have got lots of things wrong with them..." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=291s">4:51</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Describe the burdensome nature of CPR</strong></span></div><span class="verbal">"CPR is quite an invasive process... pressing on the chest very hard which can cause damage to the chest..." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=311s">5:11</a>)</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Provide a clear medical opinion based on the patient's history</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=328s">5:28</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"So what we would think about in your mum's circumstances... we would worry is that if we were to try and do CPR, that it wouldn't be effective and that it would actually end up causing more harm than good and probably wouldn't work."</span></div>
</ul>
<h4>E: Addressing Emotions with Empathic Responses</h4>
<ul>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Acknowledge and validate their concerns ("giving up")</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=393s">6:33</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"It just sounds as if you're giving up... surely it's worth trying?"</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Provide direct, empathetic reassurance</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=418s">6:58</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"I appreciate what you're saying and I just want to reassure you... that's certainly not the case."</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Acknowledge the difficulty of the conversation</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=527s">8:47</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"I appreciate that and I'm really sorry if this has come as a bit of a shock to you to have this discussion today."</span></div>
</ul>
<h4>S: Strategy and Summary</h4>
<ul>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Clarify that a DNACPR order does NOT stop other treatments</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=427s">7:07</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"In terms of treatments... none of the treatments that we would offer her change... We would still do all of the same."</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Clarify the medical team's responsibility for the decision</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=549s">9:09</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"...to take the weight off your shoulders, it's not a decision that you need to make... it's a decision that the medical team would make..."</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Check understanding by asking them to summarise (Teach-back)</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=593s">9:53</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"Is it okay if I just check what you've understood from the discussion? Would you be able to summarise it back to me?"</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Assess if they have any further questions</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=700s">11:40</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"Are you comfortable that you've had enough information from this discussion?"</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Offer additional resources</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=724s">12:04</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"I'll give you a leaflet when you leave just so that you can take that home, there's a little bit more information..."</span></div>
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"><span class="description"><strong>Close the consultation formally</strong></span> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KowT-7aEoZA&amp;t=736s">12:16</a>)</div><span class="verbal">"Thank you for taking the time to talk to me."</span></div>
</ul>
</details>
